siness","header":"Eighth-generation heir to a textile fortune","body":"Metcalf was the eldest son of the eighth American generation of his line, descended from a settler at Dedham in 1637. He led the Wanskuck Company, one of the nation's foremost woolen-fabric makers, and held directorships across banking and insurance.","number":2},{"category":"philanthropy","header":"At twenty-seven he became RISD's treasurer","body":"Elected treasurer of the Rhode Island School of Design at twenty-seven, Metcalf began a lifetime of giving to the school his family had helped found. He left his Colonial Revival mansion to RISD as its president's house.","number":3},{"category":"education","header":"A Brown man who served as trustee","body":"A graduate of Brown University in 1878, Metcalf served the school as a longtime trustee and benefactor. His brother Jesse Metcalf sat twelve years in the United States Senate.","number":4}],"sources":[],"institutions":[{"institution_id":"INST068","relationship":"alumnus and trustee","years":"1878"},{"institution_id":"INST161","relationship":"treasurer and benefactor"}],"landmarks":[{"landmark_id":"LM121","landmark_blurb":"He built this Providence mansion, later RISD’s president’s house."}],"artworks":[],"research_tags":[],"cross_connections":[{"type":"in_law","related_id":"TD0344","display_label":"married his son George"}],"quotes":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"statues":[],"bio":{"first_name":"Stephen Olney","last_name":"Metcalf","married_names":[],"display_name":"Stephen Olney Metcalf","gender":"male","photo_url":"https://res.cloudinary.com/dc5clrqtw/image/upload/v1780767435/stephenmetcalf_xejz45.png"},"military_service":[],"education":[{"institution_id":"INST068","dates":"1878","type":"college","degree":"A.B."}],"slug":"stephen-olney-metcalf-1857"},"X03122":{"id":"X03122","former_ids":[],"is_placeholder":false,"has_descendants_documented":false,"gender":"female","birth":{"year":1860,"month":11,"day":11,"city":"Providence","state":"R